      "note": "the legacy sequel about a dying magazine",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "The Devil Wears Prada 2",
          "year": 2026,
          "note": "David Frankel and Aline Brosh McKenna return; Andy Sachs comes back to Runway. It's less about fashion than about the magazine business collapsing: McKinsey, page views, a Bezos-like buyer played by Justin Theroux. Watchable and well-dressed, but more melancholy and duplicative than the original, with a Miranda who spends the film scrambling instead of cutting people down."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Devil Wears Prada",
          "year": 2006,
          "note": "The 2006 original they keep measuring it against: a movie about being good at your job, and the film that, through Miranda Priestly, ended up rehabilitating Anna Wintour."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Chandler Levack on her two 2026 films",
      "guest": "Chandler Levack on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Mile End Kicks",
          "year": 2026,
          "note": "Levack's autobiographical film about a young music writer in Montreal circa 2011; Barbie Ferreira plays a critic trying to write a 33⅓ on Alanis Morissette's 'Jagged Little Pill.' Sean, a former music journalist himself, called it uncanny."
        },
        {
          "title": "Roommates",
          "year": 2026,
          "note": "Levack's Netflix comedy from Adam Sandler's Happy Madison, starring Sadie Sandler and Chloe East as college roommates who aren't destined to stay friends."
        }
